---

<section class="problem section" aria-labelledby="problem-title">
  <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
    <h2 id="problem-title" class="problem__title">
      Specs drift. AC stay vague.<br />Agents ship the wrong thing.
    </h2>
    <p class="problem__body">
      You write the feature in the kickoff. By sprint two it's drifted —
      the AC that said <em>handles errors gracefully</em> was supposed
      to mean <em>show a toast and roll back.</em> Or was it
      <em>log and retry?</em> Nobody can find which version of the
      conversation is canonical. The spec in the doc, the thread in
      Slack, and the code in the PR have quietly disagreed for weeks.
    </p>
    <p class="problem__body">
      This was tolerable when humans read the spec — humans interpolate,
      ask, clarify. AI agents don't. They take "handles errors
      gracefully" and implement whatever pattern was most common in
      their training data. The code passes review because it does
      <strong>something</strong> sensible. It's just not what you
      meant. Multiply that across every requirement on every PR, and
      the cost adds up fast.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

